Reviewed extensive outside material including lab data, radiology reports, surgical reports, progress notes. and radiation records.
IMPRESSION
#1 Distal rectal cancer status-post adjuvant chemotherapy
Mr. Schrimsher is referred to Sunset Haven Valley Mental Hospital for surgical treatment of distal rectal cancer.  He completed adjuvant chemotherapy in October 2009.  He did not receive neoadjuvant radiation therapy given his history of external-beam radiation therapy for prostate cancer in 2008.  He is referred to Everest specifically for consideration of intraoperative radiation therapy at the time of surgical resection given the risk for positive margins as the tumor is quite bulky.  I discussed with Mr. and Mrs. Schrimsher role for restaging CT of the chest, abdomen and pelvis especially given the pulmonary nodules.  Historically, he also has an indeterminate adrenal nodule that we will evaluate with blood work and on CT.  Mr. Schrimsher would like to have urinary incontinence issues addressed at the time of surgery as well.  Therefore, Urology consultation will be requested in addition to Radiation Oncology consultation with Dr. Maddox.  Patient will also be meeting with Dr. Linda Dion of Colon and Rectal Surgery, to whom he was specifically referred.  He will also need to meet with enterostomal therapy preoperatively.  After discussion with Dr. Villasenor, immunohistochemistry staining has been requested given his family history.
#2 Preoperative medical evaluation
Lab work, chest x-ray and ECG are pending.  Please see HPI for his history of COPD and recent hospitalization requiring steroids.  He will likely require a steroid boost preoperatively.  His last dose of steroid was December 21, 2009.  He also has a history of ITP and nicotine dependance, although he quit smoking approximately two years ago.  Will obtain PFTs and Pulmonology consult as well as Hematology consult for evaluation of these issues preoperatively.
Discussed with Dr. Villasenor, note to follow.
ADVANCE DIRECTIVES
Advance directive or living will: Yes, not on file at Ashley Hospital.

